# Test import patterns

Packages build to `dist/` and export from there, so *how* a test imports a
workspace package decides what it exercises.

## Within-package tests

- **Import from source** (`../foo.ts`, `./foo.ts`) — not from the package's own
  identifier. Importing your own package by name (`@prisma/composer`) resolves to its
  built `dist/`, which is stale relative to the source you are editing.
- **Public entrypoints live under `src/exports/`** ([ADR-0035](../../docs/design/90-decisions/ADR-0035-public-entrypoints-live-in-src-exports.md)),
  so a within-package test imports an entrypoint as `../exports/<name>.ts` and an
  internal module as `../<name>.ts`. This applies to dynamic `await import('…')`
  and hardcoded filesystem paths too, not just static imports.

## Cross-package / integration tests

- **Import from the package identifier** (`@prisma/composer`, `@prisma/composer-cloud`, …)
  to verify the real public surface. This resolves to `dist/`, so the dependency
  must be built first — the `test`/`typecheck` turbo tasks build deps up front,
  and CI builds before testing (see
  [`workspace-package-not-found`](./workspace-package-not-found.mdc)).
